First Lady Melania Trump visited the New York Stock Exchange (NYSE) as part of her Be Best campaign. She rang the Opening Bell to celebrate the well-being of children, a pillar of her campaign. She was greeted by Stacey Cunningham, the President of the NYSE, who gave her a brief tour of the historic building. Melania Trump also visited the Bond Room and met with NYSE leadership. She spoke with fourth-grade students from the United Nations International School and rang the Opening Bell with them to start the day's trading session. Melania Trump expressed gratitude to the NYSE for the opportunity to ring the bell and highlighted the strength of the economic system in supporting children worldwide.